                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5801: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 9:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Irkutsk.</p>
                <p>492, December 2, 3 p.m. Vice Consul Ray reports from Novo Nikolaievsk that he is
                    evacuating. Barabinsk now in hands of Bolsheviki. General evacuation of Novo
                    Nikolaievsk begun.</p>
                <p>Vice Consul Dille reports from Taiga that General Pepelaiev intends making stand
                    Krasnoyarsk. Many soldiers in Taiga from front and in bad condition for want of
                    food. Typhus very bad there and getting worse. Czechs leave that whole
                    neighborhood with all forces in ten days. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1"
                        >Harris</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
